ce:section.ce:para:
The particle size distribution of organic nanosheets in an aqueous suspension was studied by the dynamic light scattering (DLS) method. Fig. S4 shows a narrow particle size distribution of IDP NS with an average particle size diameter of 150 nm. The SEM microphotograph of an air-dried layer of IDP NS shown in Fig. S5 signifies that aggregated particles of IDP NS having Nanoflakes and feathery type of surface morphology. The large size shown by the SEM microphotograph is due to the aggregation of nanoparticles in the clusters during sample preparation on a glass substrate for SEM analysis by evaporation of the aqueous suspension. Furthermore, photophysical properties of IDP NS in aqueous suspension were studied by UV–Vis absorption and the fluorescence spectroscopic method was given in supplementary information (
Fig. S6 to Fig. S8
). The blue-shift of absorption concerning to absorption maximum of the IDP molecule revealed to arise from possible H-bonding aggregation through π-stacking effects [43] and the enhancement of emission spectrum of IDP NS is due to restricted molecular rotations of adjacent molecules. Thus they forbid non-radiative transition and permits radiative transition of excited state nanoaggregates.
